Alright — if you want your **Home screen** to work *like Spotify*, we don’t have to limit ourselves to just FMA + IA data.
We can **mix multiple free & legal sources** so it always looks fresh and relevant without needing a giant paid backend.

Here’s the **best stack** for that:

---

## **🎯 Data Sources for Home Screen**

| Section                 | Source                                                          | Why It’s Good                         |
| ----------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| **Featured / Banner**   | **FMA curated playlists** + manually picked IA collections      | Always free, you control what appears |
| **New Releases**        | **Jamendo API** (royalty-free music) + FMA “recent tracks”      | Fresh songs every day                 |
| **Trending Now**        | **Audius API** (free music streaming platform with good search) | Active users → relevant trends        |
| **Genres You Like**     | Local genre tracking + IA “collections” by genre                | Personalized without paid DB          |
| **Recommended for You** | Tracks from same genre/artist pulled from Audius/FMA            | Lightweight personalization           |

---

## **🔹 How It Will Work in the App**

1. **Home API Aggregator**

   * Your app makes a **single call** to your small free backend (can be on **Netlify**, **Vercel**, or **GitHub Pages** JSON).
   * This backend fetches:

     * **Top trending** from Audius.
     * **Latest releases** from Jamendo.
     * **Curated free music playlists** from FMA.
     * **Hand-picked FLAC albums** from IA.
   * Merges them into a **single JSON feed**.

2. **App UI** (like Spotify)

   * **Top Banner** → Featured albums/playlists.
   * **Horizontal rows**:

     * New Releases (Jamendo + FMA)
     * Trending (Audius)
     * Recommended (Audius + FMA matching genres from user history)
     * Genres You Like (local tracking)

3. **Playback**

   * If user prefers FLAC → Check IA for that track and stream it if available.
   * If FLAC not available → Play MP3 from source API (Audius, FMA, Jamendo).

